      "message": "During CI testing, a SIGSEGV was observed at device.cpp:131. The backtrace indicates that softwareCurrent-\u003eswid became null/invalid when accessed.\n\nTo resolve this, I captured the required swid into a local variable before any potential move or state change occurs. This ensures the ID remains valid throughout the asynchronous task, and the fix has successfully passed the CI tests.\n\n\n\u0027\u0027\u0027\nProcess terminating with default action of signal 11 (SIGSEGV): dumping core\n.....\n\u003d\u003d1982\u003d\u003d by 0x17D87F: phosphor::software::device::Device::startUpdateAsync(phosphor::software::device::Device::_ZN8phosphor8software6device6Device16startUpdateAsyncEN9sdbusplus7message7details12unix_fd_typeENS3_6common3xyz15openbmc_project8software9ApplyTime19RequestedApplyTimesESt10unique_ptrINS0_8SoftwareESt14default_deleteISE_EE.Frame*) [clone .actor] (device.cpp:131)\n\u0027\u0027\u0027",
